node.text:
Vegan Banana Bread Recipe🍌🍞
-
2 sticks vegan butter 
2 cups organic brown sugar
2 tbsp egg replacer mix (we used Rob’s Red Mill)
2 tsp water 
2 1/2 cups cups mashed banana
1/4 tsp vanilla extract
3 cups sifted flour
1/2 tsp salt 
2 tsp baking soda 
Optional 1 c chopped walnuts
-
Preheat oven to 350 F. Sift together flour, salt and baking soda and set aside. Melt butter and mix the butter and sugar until well blended. Add egg substitute servings one at a time to the butter and sugar mixture. Add bananas and vanilla. Fold in flour mixture and optional walnuts. Mix well until blended and moist. Grease 2 large loaf pans or several mini loaf pans with a baking spray. Divide batter equally. Bake for 45 minutes or until the center of the loaves are firm and a toothpick in the center comes out clean (no batter should be on the toothpick!) Let cool and enjoy ☺️🍌🍞

node.title: Making Vegan Banana Bread with My Mom

node.text: As you all know, The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel is one of my absolute favorite shows, so when Amazon asked me to come down to Miami to celebrate the new season I was SO excited. ☺️ I had such an amazing time at the Fontainebleau (the same hotel season 3 was shot in!) to celebrate season 3 premiere of @maiseltv. Throughout December, Amazon Prime Video and Fontainebleau are offering guests “marvelous packages.” I got a pedicure, massage, and had some of the best drinks & dinner during my stay here (check my stories to see what I’ve been up to!) Season 3 premieres today on @amazonprimevideo! ❤️🍸🎺#MrsMaisel

node.text: Gratitude is such a powerful energy…if you’re feeling lost, confused, stuck, take out a pen and write down everything you’re grateful for. Release anything that you feel is weighing your energy down. There’s always something to be grateful for, whether it be your health, a place you got to travel to, a person that loves you, a job you have. Gratitude propels you forward into abundance. Sending you all love 🌗💕

node.text: I missed you sooo much New York. (the last slide is my fave moment ever, it was so peaceful last night. I went to dinner by the water right before it started pouring) 🌝 you would have no idea I have a stomach parasite from Mexico the last few days and have been dying bahahaha. I do my best to push through and distract myself through nature, works every time. 🍃
